# Update fleet skills and prompts

## Step

Resolved when a sweep of `~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard` (fleet graft
blocks in `scripts/fleet/`, `TOOLS.md`, `STACK.md`, skills) plus the
fleet-relevant skills in `~/.claude/skills/` and joelclaw repo docs
(`CLAUDE.md` key-paths table, `AGENTS.md`, `skills/`) finds no live
reference to: the system log as a working surface
(`~/Vault/system/system-log.jsonl`, `slog`), `memory_observations` /
old `joelclaw recall` semantics, Chorus/rhizomatic briefings as a live
injection, or Claude auto-memory as a content store. Each reference is
updated to the new reality (recall = Brain-backed; retros = hook-fired
Inngest event; MEMORY.md = pointer index) or marked historical. Changes
are committed and pushed in their repos, `fleet-graft.sh install` run so
graft blocks refresh, and a `dw-sync` drift report comes back clean.
Steering commits; ShitRat rules apply for any GitHub-bound pushes.
Serialized behind the retirement and Chorus steps — document what IS.
